docs.text: About The Author Introduction My name is Hasan, I am overtly passionate about computer science, so please excuse the excitement and occasional ramblings. By day I work on the AWS application migration efforts of the North Star 21 initiative, by night I help teach students at Franklin University Object Oriented Programming and Data Structures. In my free time I enjoy to miserably fail at trying to convince my wife and 3 children they love computer science as much as I do. Some other hobbies include; archery, yoyos, and watching movies that are soo terrible they are wonderful! Favorite Quote: "Computer science is no more about computers than astronomy is about telescopes" - Edsger Dijkstra
